      <div class="volume-bar"><span class="volume-label">PhotosNew</span><div class="volume-fill" style="width:0.01%;background:#6a8ad6;"></div><span class="volume-count">224</span></div>
      <div class="volume-bar"><span class="volume-label" style="color:#6d6;">Models</span><div class="volume-fill" style="width:1.3%;background:linear-gradient(90deg,#6ad68a,#4a9a6a);"></div><span class="volume-count"><%= stats.models ? stats.models.toLocaleString() : '—' %></span></div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:11px;color:#555;margin-top:16px;">Graph pattern: <code style="color:#8af;">http://localhost:3000/pods/jeff/media/{Volume}</code></p>
  </div>

  <!-- Architecture Notes -->
  <div class="section full-width">
    <h2>Persistence Architecture</h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr;gap:20px;font-size:13px;">
      <div>
        <div style="color:#6af;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:8px;">Storage Model</div>
        <div style="color:#aaa;">Collection-graph sharding — one named graph per volume. 26 graphs vs 1.85M alternative (graph-per-entity). 121x faster writes, zero query degradation on existing queries.</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div style="color:#6af;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:8px;">Fuseki Capacity</div>
        <div style="color:#aaa;">13.3M triples / 4,488 graphs total. 1GB JVM heap. Bulk writes chunked at 100K items to prevent OOM. Music queries 231ms post-harvest (no degradation).</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div style="color:#6af;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:8px;">Data Flow</div>
        <div style="color:#aaa;">MongoDB (secondary Mac) &#8594; SSH + mongosh TTL export &#8594; HTTP PUT/POST (GSP) &#8594; Fuseki named graph. 22 min full harvest. Script: architect/scripts/harvest-media.sh</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:40px;font-size:11px;color:#444;">
  jb-ontology.ttl v1.1.0 &#183; 241 declarations (70 classes, 54 object props, 117 datatype props) &#183; Cards #224 #375 #376
</p>

</div>
